1
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:55,179
FREE LOVE

2
00:02:27,507 --> 00:02:28,474
Miss Fifine!

3
00:02:28,675 --> 00:02:29,733
Fifine!

4
00:02:30,109 --> 00:02:31,076
Fifine!

5
00:02:31,277 --> 00:02:32,574
Miss Fifine!

6
00:02:32,979 --> 00:02:34,446
Fifine?

7
00:02:38,451 --> 00:02:39,679
Fifine?

8
00:02:45,158 --> 00:02:46,455
Fifine.

9
00:03:03,309 --> 00:03:05,300
Fifine disappeared.

10
00:03:06,246 --> 00:03:09,306
Maybe he's killing himself
for a fling.

11
00:03:10,617 --> 00:03:14,610
It all started a month ago,
when my grandmother died.

12
00:03:14,821 --> 00:03:18,154
and Miguel, the notary, said
that we would only open the will...

13
00:03:18,358 --> 00:03:21,054
in the presence of his
two other grandchildren...

14
00:03:21,261 --> 00:03:23,752
my cousins
Jean-Paul and Séraphine...

15
00:03:23,963 --> 00:03:26,989
disappeared since the great
family feud of 1942.

16
00:03:28,101 --> 00:03:32,094
Miguel looked for them.
29 days passed.

17
00:03:35,875 --> 00:03:37,706
Hello?
Hello, Cesar?

18
00:03:38,011 --> 00:03:39,774
Good morning, Mr. Miguel.

19
00:03:39,979 --> 00:03:41,207
Yes.

20
00:03:41,414 --> 00:03:42,472
Yes.

21
00:03:42,682 --> 00:03:45,412
I think Miss Miléna
is in her room.

22
00:03:45,618 --> 00:03:47,779
Yes. I'm going to play there.

23
00:03:49,355 --> 00:03:50,617
What's that?

24
00:03:50,823 --> 00:03:52,723
Mr. Cesar, the new chambermaid.

25
00:03:52,925 --> 00:03:55,223
I'll take care of you.

26
00:03:58,331 --> 00:03:59,730
Yes?

27
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:01,760
Go ahead.

28
00:04:03,403 --> 00:04:05,598
- Hello, Miguel?
- Miléna?

29
00:04:05,805 --> 00:04:07,432
I found it.

30
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:09,198
They were traveling.

31
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:12,935
I have all the information.

32
00:04:13,146 --> 00:04:14,511
Just a moment.

33
00:04:18,985 --> 00:04:20,247
That's it.

34
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:23,518
"Jean-Paul Brett-Juval,
was born in Washington...

35
00:04:23,723 --> 00:04:26,715
on March 15, 1930,
lives in Paris, etc.

36
00:04:26,926 --> 00:04:29,190
Current address
Rue de Berry, 144.

37
00:04:29,395 --> 00:04:32,762
Fashion photographer,
manager of the Omnia Mode agency.

38
00:04:32,965 --> 00:04:35,365
Séraphine Brett-Juval,
Jean-Paul's younger sister.

39
00:04:35,568 --> 00:04:39,299
She was born in Washington in 1939,
where she lived until her mother's death...

40
00:04:39,505 --> 00:04:41,166
in 1956.

41
00:04:41,374 --> 00:04:43,171
He lived in Paris with his brother...

42
00:04:43,376 --> 00:04:46,368
lives at 46 Rue Jacob,
with Mr. Robert Godard...

43
00:04:46,579 --> 00:04:51,346
fashion photographer,
an associate of the aforementioned."

44
00:04:51,751 --> 00:04:54,743
What a relief, Miguel.
I thought I'd never find them.

45
00:04:54,954 --> 00:04:56,819
Your cousin is in Biarritz...

46
00:04:57,023 --> 00:05:00,481
at the Hotel Du Palais,
where I spoke to him.

47
00:05:01,027 --> 00:05:03,291
He might come on Friday.

48
00:05:03,496 --> 00:05:07,057
Are you arriving on Friday?
Do you know what time?

49
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,267
It's all right.

50
00:05:09,469 --> 00:05:10,959
Call again.

51
00:05:11,804 --> 00:05:13,965
Thanks and see you later, Miguel.

52
00:05:17,176 --> 00:05:19,474
You can call me Mr. Cesar.

53
00:05:19,679 --> 00:05:21,977
Yes, Mr. Cesar.
But I'll say "you".

54
00:05:22,181 --> 00:05:25,378
If you're going to start,
I'll throw you out now.

55
00:05:25,585 --> 00:05:28,577
- So I'm calm.
- Why is that?

56
00:05:28,788 --> 00:05:31,052
By the way you look at me.

57
00:05:32,058 --> 00:05:33,582
If you are...

58
00:05:34,494 --> 00:05:36,121
very kind...

59
00:05:36,729 --> 00:05:39,061
we'll manage.

60
00:05:39,732 --> 00:05:41,393
I'm a young woman.

61
00:05:43,202 --> 00:05:45,432
- Are you laughing at me?
- No, Mr. Cesar.

62
00:05:45,638 --> 00:05:47,629
I say I'm young.

63
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:49,068
Good.

64
00:05:51,177 --> 00:05:53,077
Rosa will show you
her room...

65
00:05:53,279 --> 00:05:56,715
and when she's settled in,
you will see Miss Miléna.

66
00:06:16,502 --> 00:06:19,471
What will you do with the money?
when you have it?

67
00:06:19,672 --> 00:06:23,199
- I'm going to buy a "ganadería".
- A what?

68
00:06:23,409 --> 00:06:25,240
Bull breeding.

69
00:06:25,445 --> 00:06:28,846
- I forgot you were an aficionado.
- Aficionado.

70
00:06:30,516 --> 00:06:32,814
Robert, let's be serious.

71
00:06:35,288 --> 00:06:38,519
We're going to have to delay our
to Cadequés by three days.

72
00:06:38,724 --> 00:06:40,316
You mean?

73
00:06:41,327 --> 00:06:43,625
You're taking me to Perpignan...

74
00:06:43,830 --> 00:06:46,628
- And, or wait for me for three days...
- Lovely.

75
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:50,963
...or go straight to Cadequés
and I'll come to you.

76
00:06:51,170 --> 00:06:53,502
I'm sure you'll find a girl
to wait for me.

77
00:06:53,706 --> 00:06:55,230
And Jean-Paul?

78
00:06:55,441 --> 00:06:57,671
He'll be arriving from Biarritz.

79
00:06:57,877 --> 00:06:59,674
I'll make an appointment
with him in Perpignan...

80
00:06:59,879 --> 00:07:01,870
and he'll take me to the castle.

81
00:07:02,081 --> 00:07:04,948
Are you ashamed
to come with me to the castle?

82
00:07:05,151 --> 00:07:08,314
I don't want to show up
as a boyfriend.

83
00:07:08,521 --> 00:07:11,581
You know, cousin Miléna
must be the type...

84
00:07:11,791 --> 00:07:14,851
provincial spinster,
all stuck up and stuff.

85
00:07:15,061 --> 00:07:18,258
As you wish. But I warn you
that if you find a girl...

86
00:07:18,464 --> 00:07:20,489
I recommended it myself.

87
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:24,534
I know our agreement.
Everyone has their freedom.

88
00:07:33,145 --> 00:07:36,308
Good morning, miss.
I'll take care of the luggage.

89
00:07:36,516 --> 00:07:37,915
Thank you.

90
00:07:41,787 --> 00:07:42,981
Séraphine?

91
00:07:43,189 --> 00:07:45,123
- Nice to meet you.
- Me too, Miléna.

92
00:07:45,324 --> 00:07:47,053
- Kiss?
- Yes.

93
00:07:47,927 --> 00:07:49,861
You speak
French very well.

94
00:07:50,062 --> 00:07:52,326
I've been in France
for three years now.

95
00:07:52,532 --> 00:07:56,332
Prudence will show you to your room.
Didn't your brother come along?

96
00:07:56,536 --> 00:08:00,336
No. I came from Paris...
with a friend.

97
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:02,132
We slept in Perpignan.

98
00:08:02,341 --> 00:08:05,242
My brother was supposed to meet me
at the hotel, but he didn't show up.

99
00:08:05,444 --> 00:08:07,207
- No?
- But it won't be long.

100
00:09:10,977 --> 00:09:12,001
What do you want?

101
00:09:12,511 --> 00:09:15,446
- Ms. Brett-Juval, please?
- From whom?

102
00:09:15,648 --> 00:09:18,742
I... say it's from
her brother's.

103
00:09:18,951 --> 00:09:21,249
- Yes. It's Mr. Jean-Paul.
- Don't!

104
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:48,837
Jean-Paul?

105
00:10:00,359 --> 00:10:01,951
Jean-Paul?

106
00:10:04,296 --> 00:10:05,285
Yes.

107
00:10:09,502 --> 00:10:12,300
Miléna.
I didn't recognize you, Jean-Paul.

108
00:10:13,039 --> 00:10:14,631
Not either, Miléna.

109
00:10:15,775 --> 00:10:18,869
The last time we saw each other,
I was one year old.

110
00:10:19,278 --> 00:10:20,745
Of course.

111
00:10:22,615 --> 00:10:25,049
Your sister has arrived.
She didn't see you in Perpignan.

112
00:10:25,251 --> 00:10:28,778
Yes. I was late.
I'd like to see you.

113
00:10:28,988 --> 00:10:31,252
I think he's in his room,
taking a shower.

114
00:10:31,457 --> 00:10:34,654
Prudence will show you her room.
It's next to hers.

115
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:37,124
Good morning.
Who is she?

116
00:10:37,329 --> 00:10:40,355
She's the cook's granddaughter.
She's on vacation here.

117
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:44,931
When dinner is ready,
I'll send for you.

118
00:10:45,137 --> 00:10:48,368
Cesar. Do you want to look after
Mr. Jean-Paul?

119
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:15,396
It was your father's
of your father.

120
00:11:15,601 --> 00:11:17,398
There's no shortage of places.

121
00:11:17,603 --> 00:11:21,061
It was always called
the room of the Borgia.

122
00:11:21,273 --> 00:11:23,241
- That's right.
- You know, Mr. Jean-Paul...

123
00:11:23,442 --> 00:11:28,106
it was a family joke.
Someone must have said it, and it stuck.

124
00:11:28,314 --> 00:11:29,611
And what is it called?

125
00:11:29,815 --> 00:11:30,873
Cesar.

126
00:11:31,083 --> 00:11:33,881
- Cesar?
- Cesar. Excuse me.

127
00:11:34,086 --> 00:11:35,781
Well done, Cesar.

128
00:11:37,323 --> 00:11:39,416
- The suitcases...
- No, that's fine.

129
00:11:39,625 --> 00:11:40,683
No.

130
00:11:40,893 --> 00:11:45,523
- The bathroom is at the back, on the right.
- Perfect.

131
00:11:45,731 --> 00:11:47,699
- You don't need me anymore?
- No, you don't.

132
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,993
Tell me. Where is
my sister's room?

133
00:11:50,202 --> 00:11:52,830
- It's the fourth Chinese.
- Chinese?

134
00:11:53,038 --> 00:11:55,871
That's it. You'll understand,
when you see it.

135
00:11:56,075 --> 00:11:58,635
Third door on the right.
Do you know it?

136
00:11:58,844 --> 00:12:00,311
- You're welcome.
- You're welcome.

137
00:12:00,513 --> 00:12:02,743
Dinner is at eight.

138
00:12:02,948 --> 00:12:05,678
- If Mr. Miguel isn't late.
- I'll be ready.

139
00:12:05,885 --> 00:12:07,853
Thank you very much. Thank you very much.

140
00:12:23,335 --> 00:12:24,927
Yes. Come in.

141
00:12:46,158 --> 00:12:47,955
Robert? You here?

142
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,752
Yes, as you can see.

143
00:12:49,962 --> 00:12:52,362
What happened?
I forbade you to come.

144
00:12:52,565 --> 00:12:54,032
You don't forbid me anything.

145
00:12:54,233 --> 00:12:57,566
And when you left,
your brother called.

146
00:12:57,770 --> 00:12:59,863
- So what?
- He won't be here until Monday.

147
00:13:00,072 --> 00:13:02,199
The whole team went to Spain.

148
00:13:02,408 --> 00:13:03,670
That's great.

149
00:13:03,876 --> 00:13:06,037
I've come to tell you
what to say to your cousin.

150
00:13:06,245 --> 00:13:08,406
The truth, of course.

151
00:13:08,614 --> 00:13:11,208
- Difficult.
- What do you mean, difficult?

152
00:13:11,417 --> 00:13:14,978
- I'll tell you.
- Have you been up to something?

153
00:13:16,422 --> 00:13:18,390
Yeah, it sounds like a joke.

154
00:13:18,591 --> 00:13:20,991
When I arrived, the chambermaid
took me for Jean-Paul.

155
00:13:21,193 --> 00:13:22,455
- Jean-Paul?
- Yes.

156
00:13:22,661 --> 00:13:25,061
And the worst thing is that his cousin
took me for him too.

157
00:13:25,264 --> 00:13:27,494
- It's not true.
- It's the pure truth.

158
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:29,292
And you didn't explain?

159
00:13:29,501 --> 00:13:32,095
I haven't explained anything.
She thinks I'm Jean-Paul.

160
00:13:32,304 --> 00:13:35,569
You're completely crazy.
Why did you do that?

161
00:13:35,774 --> 00:13:37,969
I don't know.
I thought it was funny.

162
00:13:38,677 --> 00:13:42,169
- Is it the cousin you like?
- The cousin?

163
00:13:42,648 --> 00:13:45,208
Don't play the fool.
I know you.

164
00:13:45,417 --> 00:13:47,385
It's not the first time
you've done that to me.

165
00:13:47,586 --> 00:13:49,178
What about our agreement?

166
00:13:49,455 --> 00:13:52,151
Listen. They're calling us to dinner
in five minutes.

167
00:13:52,358 --> 00:13:54,189
Perfect. I'm hungry.

168
00:13:54,393 --> 00:13:56,918
- Do you make fun of me?
- Not at all.

169
00:13:57,129 --> 00:13:59,154
It's not a tragedy
me having dinner here.

170
00:13:59,365 --> 00:14:03,131
Very well. When we're
at the table, I'll explain to Miléna.

171
00:14:03,335 --> 00:14:06,498
- Give me one night.
- Not at all, Robert.

172
00:14:06,705 --> 00:14:09,970
I'll explain everything. And now.

173
00:14:10,175 --> 00:14:12,075
Don't do that.

174
00:14:12,278 --> 00:14:13,711
You'll see.

175
00:14:19,018 --> 00:14:21,452
I tried to call
to say I was going to be late...

176
00:14:21,654 --> 00:14:24,487
- but your line is faulty.
- Good.

177
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:29,718
Cesar didn't say anything.
It's a thread. This is Mr. Miguel Barran.

178
00:14:29,929 --> 00:14:31,157
My cousin Séraphine.

179
00:14:31,363 --> 00:14:33,024
- Good evening, miss.
- Good night, ma'am.

180
00:14:33,232 --> 00:14:35,359
Jean-Paul, Miguel Barran.

181
00:14:37,503 --> 00:14:39,869
- Good evening, sir.
- Good night, sir.

182
00:14:40,306 --> 00:14:43,036
- That'll do, Cesar.
- Yes, miss.

183
00:14:43,876 --> 00:14:46,106
Jean-Paul, on my right.

184
00:14:46,979 --> 00:14:49,243
Séraphine, Miguel.

185
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:56,413
Robert?

186
00:15:59,051 --> 00:16:00,416
Robert.

187
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:04,953
- My name is Jean-Paul.
- Please, I don't want to laugh.

188
00:16:05,157 --> 00:16:07,216
So. What happens then?

189
00:16:07,426 --> 00:16:09,223
- I'm afraid.
- Of what?

190
00:16:09,428 --> 00:16:12,795
- The Chinese room scares me.
- You're not five anymore.

191
00:16:12,998 --> 00:16:15,432
Yes, but that's not all.

192
00:16:16,468 --> 00:16:18,834
- I'm worried.
- Worried?

193
00:16:19,038 --> 00:16:21,563
Yes, with the lies.
That's going to end badly.

194
00:16:21,774 --> 00:16:25,232
No. When Jean-Paul arrives,
we'll just laugh it off.

195
00:16:25,444 --> 00:16:26,911
Not me.

196
00:16:27,112 --> 00:16:29,580
- Why didn't you say anything then?
- I don't know.

197
00:16:30,349 --> 00:16:33,546
- Did you like the notary?
- Are you crazy?

198
00:16:33,752 --> 00:16:36,118
And that
is also in our agreement.

199
00:16:36,321 --> 00:16:39,779
I'll help you if you help me,
but right now, I'm sleepy.

200
00:16:39,992 --> 00:16:42,984
- I want to be with you.
- No way.

201
00:16:44,263 --> 00:16:47,391
- If you don't want to, I'll tell you everything.
- Nice.

202
00:16:47,599 --> 00:16:49,692
- Be kind.
- Don't.

203
00:16:50,335 --> 00:16:52,428
And he says he loves me.

204
00:16:52,638 --> 00:16:54,572
Did I say that?

205
00:16:54,773 --> 00:16:58,470
Well done. Since that's the case,
I won't go to Cadequés.

206
00:16:58,677 --> 00:16:59,871
Good.

207
00:17:06,852 --> 00:17:08,820
A girl.

208
00:18:38,076 --> 00:18:39,600
Yes?

209
00:19:04,369 --> 00:19:07,304
- Good morning, Mr. Jean-Paul.
- Good morning, Cesar.

210
00:19:07,506 --> 00:19:10,270
- Did you sleep well?
- Very well.

211
00:19:10,475 --> 00:19:12,102
The weather looks good.

212
00:19:12,311 --> 00:19:14,871
It's always good weather here,
sir.

213
00:19:15,447 --> 00:19:17,972
You don't seem to like it here.

214
00:19:18,183 --> 00:19:20,117
I can say that, in general...

215
00:19:20,319 --> 00:19:22,344
and with all due respect...

216
00:19:22,554 --> 00:19:24,784
I'm deeply bored.

217
00:19:24,990 --> 00:19:27,117
- Have you been here long?
- Ten years.

218
00:19:27,326 --> 00:19:29,521
You must miss
distractions.

219
00:19:29,728 --> 00:19:31,855
Only one thing interests me.

220
00:19:32,064 --> 00:19:33,588
Women.

221
00:19:34,366 --> 00:19:37,130
I don't see anything wrong with that, Cesar.
On the contrary.

222
00:19:37,336 --> 00:19:39,600
Recruitment here
can't be easy.

223
00:19:39,805 --> 00:19:42,103
- I have a trick.
- A trick?

224
00:19:42,307 --> 00:19:43,331
That's it.

225
00:19:43,542 --> 00:19:47,444
Lady Henriette gave me freedom
in personnel matters.

226
00:19:47,646 --> 00:19:50,843
For example, I'm
who employs the chambermaids.

227
00:19:51,049 --> 00:19:53,017
- Do you understand?
- Very well.

228
00:19:53,218 --> 00:19:57,484
I choose a local one,
one I like, of course...

229
00:19:57,689 --> 00:19:58,986
e...

230
00:20:01,593 --> 00:20:04,027
- And if she resists...
- I'll put it out the door.

231
00:20:04,229 --> 00:20:05,253
Really?

232
00:20:05,464 --> 00:20:08,661
- What if I want to get married?
- I won't allow it, Mr. Jean-Paul.

233
00:20:08,867 --> 00:20:10,732
They end up marrying
someone local.

234
00:20:10,936 --> 00:20:12,699
Having served here is a benchmark.

235
00:20:12,904 --> 00:20:15,737
No. What I like is change.

236
00:20:15,941 --> 00:20:18,501
If any of them get attached to me,
I'll throw them out.

237
00:20:18,710 --> 00:20:21,440
Congratulations, Cesar.
You're a Casanova.

238
00:20:21,647 --> 00:20:24,445
By the way,
your latest hire.

239
00:20:24,650 --> 00:20:26,515
- Not bad.
- What's not bad?

240
00:20:26,852 --> 00:20:28,410
But it won't be easy.

241
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:29,609
No?

242
00:20:29,821 --> 00:20:34,087
She's only been here for three days
and I haven't had much time for her...

243
00:20:37,129 --> 00:20:39,723
but I have the impression
it won't be easy at all.

244
00:20:39,931 --> 00:20:42,229
Come on, Cesar, you don't have to
lose your self-confidence.

245
00:20:42,434 --> 00:20:44,095
Of course.

246
00:20:44,303 --> 00:20:46,430
Of course. But I'll try
anyway. That's for sure.

247
00:20:46,638 --> 00:20:49,436
- Good luck, Cesar.
- Thank you, Mr. Jean-Paul.

248
00:20:49,641 --> 00:20:52,633
May I remind
to Mr. Jean-Paul...

249
00:20:52,844 --> 00:20:55,438
he has a meeting
in the library at 10am.

250
00:20:55,647 --> 00:20:58,582
THE KING OF MODELS

251
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:07,715
Come on.

252
00:21:10,729 --> 00:21:13,755
Prudence, I see you
out of commission.

253
00:21:14,366 --> 00:21:15,958
I was waiting for your orders.

254
00:21:16,168 --> 00:21:18,693
Get the trays,
to get busy.

255
00:21:20,772 --> 00:21:22,501
Yes, Mr. Cesar.

256
00:21:26,244 --> 00:21:27,677
Come in.

257
00:21:42,994 --> 00:21:44,484
ROBERT GODARD
PHOTOGRAPHER

258
00:21:44,696 --> 00:21:46,254
What's wrong?

259
00:21:47,532 --> 00:21:50,160
Nothing. I've come for the tray.

260
00:22:05,984 --> 00:22:08,111
On the table, Cesar.

261
00:22:13,425 --> 00:22:15,290
Thank you, Cesar.

262
00:22:19,231 --> 00:22:22,428
First, I'd like to thank
Miguel's presence.

263
00:22:22,634 --> 00:22:26,297
You may not know it, but you read
a will in the notary's office.

264
00:22:26,505 --> 00:22:28,496
It's nothing, Miléna.

265
00:22:30,575 --> 00:22:33,442
I gathered them here, as notary public
of Lady Henriette...

266
00:22:33,645 --> 00:22:36,478
who died on June 16th
1959, in this castle.

267
00:22:36,681 --> 00:22:39,707
She appointed me
her executor.

268
00:22:40,585 --> 00:22:43,713
I will read the
she has made.

269
00:22:51,196 --> 00:22:53,528
"This is my will.
I, the undersigned...

270
00:22:53,732 --> 00:22:56,860
Henriette Amélie Jeanne Juval,
widow of Sir John Brett...

271
00:22:57,068 --> 00:22:59,969
- killed on June 18, 1917..."
- What?

272
00:23:00,172 --> 00:23:01,332
The pencils.

273
00:23:01,540 --> 00:23:03,269
I've never forgotten.

274
00:23:03,475 --> 00:23:06,376
At the Council meetings
chaired by Lady Henriette...

275
00:23:06,578 --> 00:23:09,411
- It's okay, Cesar.
- I'd put the pencils in.

276
00:23:09,614 --> 00:23:13,880
So I don't see why
I wouldn't continue...

277
00:23:14,085 --> 00:23:15,677
putting...

278
00:23:15,887 --> 00:23:18,685
the pencils. There it is.
Nothing missing?

279
00:23:18,890 --> 00:23:21,620
It's all right.
Leave us, Cesar, please.

280
00:23:27,199 --> 00:23:29,724
"I make the following
as follows:

281
00:23:29,935 --> 00:23:33,871
I appoint universal legatees,
jointly for the whole...

282
00:23:34,072 --> 00:23:37,405
or separately, for a third,
my three grandchildren, namely...

283
00:23:37,609 --> 00:23:40,305
Jean-Paul Eric Pierre
Brett-Juval...

284
00:23:40,512 --> 00:23:42,605
Séraphine Alexandra
Brett-Juval...

285
00:23:42,814 --> 00:23:44,805
Miléna Françoise
Brett-Juval...

286
00:23:45,016 --> 00:23:47,450
who are in charge of
distributing the following...

287
00:23:49,888 --> 00:23:50,946
Mr. Cesar?

288
00:23:51,156 --> 00:23:53,215
- What do you want?
- It's ugly to listen like that.

289
00:23:53,425 --> 00:23:56,588
Mind your own business.
I want to know what's going on.

290
00:23:56,962 --> 00:23:59,863
I never do that
and I know everything.

291
00:24:02,901 --> 00:24:05,028
"Made, written and dated
by my hands...

292
00:24:05,237 --> 00:24:07,603
healthy in body and spirit
in my castle of Aubarède...

293
00:24:07,806 --> 00:24:10,798
in 1957, November 2nd.

294
00:24:11,343 --> 00:24:13,777
Signed:
Henriette Brett-Juval."

295
00:24:15,981 --> 00:24:17,608
From reading...

296
00:24:17,816 --> 00:24:20,512
except for the legacies
Casaneuve, Lerbier and Loinod...

297
00:24:20,719 --> 00:24:23,916
and taking into account the other
legacies mentioned...

298
00:24:24,122 --> 00:24:27,558
the total amount of which is
six million francs...

299
00:24:27,759 --> 00:24:30,284
and taking into account
of Lady Henriette...

300
00:24:30,495 --> 00:24:34,363
to leave the Cardonna couple
the use of the Cedars Pavilion...

301
00:24:34,566 --> 00:24:38,297
in Sainte Marguerite
and two hectares around it...

302
00:24:38,503 --> 00:24:40,835
results, I said, from reading...

303
00:24:41,039 --> 00:24:44,497
that Lady Henriette leaves all
her estate in equal shares...

304
00:24:44,709 --> 00:24:49,840
to the three grandchildren present:
Séraphine, Jean-Paul and Miléna.

305
00:24:50,582 --> 00:24:54,746
There you go. It's hard to say what
these assets represent.

306
00:24:54,953 --> 00:24:57,820
However, it is my duty...

307
00:24:58,023 --> 00:25:01,322
let them know that the
of these assets...

308
00:25:01,526 --> 00:25:03,687
- is minimal.
- But business is good.

309
00:25:03,895 --> 00:25:05,726
- Quite well.
- Yes, but the profits...

310
00:25:05,931 --> 00:25:07,990
have been reinvested
for six years...

311
00:25:08,199 --> 00:25:12,101
to finance equipment
and a reserve fund.

312
00:25:12,804 --> 00:25:15,034
I mean, it's no good.

313
00:25:16,207 --> 00:25:18,505
In the long term,
its parts are realizable.

314
00:25:18,710 --> 00:25:20,109
And then there's the castle.

315
00:25:20,312 --> 00:25:21,301
The castle?

316
00:25:21,513 --> 00:25:23,572
Yes, the castle
now belongs to you...

317
00:25:23,782 --> 00:25:25,977
and his brother and cousin.

318
00:25:26,184 --> 00:25:28,448
Your only two problems,
at the moment...

319
00:25:28,653 --> 00:25:32,589
are the problem
of inheritance rights...

320
00:25:32,791 --> 00:25:34,884
and what to do with the castle,
between the three of you.

321
00:25:35,260 --> 00:25:39,196
- Is he sellable?
- Hardly. Certainly below his value.

322
00:25:39,397 --> 00:25:41,831
I think Miléna
should decide.

323
00:25:42,033 --> 00:25:44,433
Does she want to continue
to live here?

324
00:25:45,303 --> 00:25:47,703
You know, it's only been a month...

325
00:25:47,906 --> 00:25:50,966
It's hard for me to leave,
sentimentally.

326
00:25:51,176 --> 00:25:54,475
Of course. There's no hurry.
That's all there is to it.

327
00:25:54,679 --> 00:25:57,147
In fact, nothing will be decided
before Monday.

328
00:25:57,349 --> 00:25:59,510
You have to look at the banks
and each of the accounts.

329
00:25:59,718 --> 00:26:02,812
It's only Saturday.
And there's a selection tomorrow.

330
00:26:03,021 --> 00:26:04,852
- There's what?
- Rugby, my dear.

331
00:26:05,056 --> 00:26:06,853
He's the coach of a team.

332
00:26:07,058 --> 00:26:10,687
The winter round is coming
and Miguel would never miss it.

333
00:26:10,895 --> 00:26:14,422
Don't be unfair, Miléna. I can be
at your disposal tomorrow, if you like...

334
00:26:14,633 --> 00:26:16,726
but I don't see the point.

335
00:26:17,202 --> 00:26:19,067
Are there any races in the region?

336
00:26:19,270 --> 00:26:22,171
- Races?
- Yes. Fifine loves bullfighting.

337
00:26:22,374 --> 00:26:25,832
Actually, there's one tomorrow.
If you like, I can accompany you.

338
00:26:26,044 --> 00:26:28,740
What about your rugby, Miguel?

339
00:26:29,547 --> 00:26:31,139
I also like bulls.

340
00:26:38,023 --> 00:26:41,618
They stayed at the table
14 minutes longer than yesterday.

341
00:26:41,826 --> 00:26:44,488
- Do you time your meals now?
- Always.

342
00:26:44,696 --> 00:26:47,790
This proves that they are
getting to know each other better.

343
00:26:47,999 --> 00:26:50,467
You're clever, Cesar, you know that?

344
00:26:51,336 --> 00:26:52,928
Smart.

345
00:27:01,613 --> 00:27:03,740
Mr. Cesar. Can you do that now?

346
00:27:04,816 --> 00:27:07,410
I like you. Very much so.

347
00:27:07,619 --> 00:27:09,712
Is Mr. Cesar crazy?

348
00:27:11,356 --> 00:27:15,224
- Call me Cesar.
- Aren't you ashamed, Mr. Cesar?

349
00:27:30,742 --> 00:27:32,835
- Do we swim in it?
- Yes.

350
00:27:33,044 --> 00:27:34,671
The water is not very clean.

351
00:27:34,879 --> 00:27:38,110
The system is old.
Each time is different.

352
00:27:38,783 --> 00:27:42,275
Tell me, Miléna.
Who is this Miguel?

353
00:27:43,121 --> 00:27:44,452
Miguel?

354
00:27:44,656 --> 00:27:46,214
Yes. Who is it?

355
00:27:46,424 --> 00:27:48,153
He's a curious man.

356
00:27:48,359 --> 00:27:50,589
Curious? Miguel?

357
00:27:50,829 --> 00:27:54,265
- Does that make the clock work?
- Yes, it does.

358
00:27:55,934 --> 00:27:57,925
And this is for climbing
on the roof?

359
00:27:58,136 --> 00:28:01,037
No. It's to go to the tower.
Do you want to go up to the roof?

360
00:28:01,239 --> 00:28:03,901
- I'd like to.
- This way. Come along.

361
00:28:06,978 --> 00:28:09,446
- And when did he show up?
- Miguel?

362
00:28:10,582 --> 00:28:14,143
When he returned from Indochina. His father
bought him a notary's office in Perpignan...

363
00:28:14,352 --> 00:28:16,343
and a grandmother chose him as her favorite.

364
00:28:16,554 --> 00:28:19,250
And Fifine and me,
she never talked about?

365
00:28:19,457 --> 00:28:20,685
Never.

366
00:28:20,892 --> 00:28:24,453
Since the fight in 1942,
he has given up on his family.

367
00:28:24,662 --> 00:28:27,256
His real children
were Michael and me.

368
00:28:27,866 --> 00:28:30,061
And she never thought...

369
00:28:30,268 --> 00:28:31,758
Yes.

370
00:28:31,970 --> 00:28:34,438
- So what?
- Then nothing.

371
00:28:34,639 --> 00:28:37,039
And it's none of your business.

372
00:28:37,242 --> 00:28:39,335
Why? Between cousins...

373
00:28:39,544 --> 00:28:41,512
There is no interest.

374
00:28:41,713 --> 00:28:45,114
One day, Miguel and I stopped
understand each other. That's all.

375
00:28:45,316 --> 00:28:47,580
- Just like that? One day, abruptly?
- Yes.

376
00:28:48,653 --> 00:28:50,211
Like this.

377
00:28:50,989 --> 00:28:52,479
One day.

378
00:28:53,758 --> 00:28:54,554
Suddenly.

379
00:28:59,664 --> 00:29:02,497
What's the matter, Miléna?
Don't you feel well?

380
00:29:02,700 --> 00:29:04,429
It's nothing.

381
00:29:04,636 --> 00:29:06,297
Let's go back, Jean-Paul.

382
00:29:06,504 --> 00:29:08,938
I still have to answer
to letters of condolence.

383
00:29:09,140 --> 00:29:10,869
Can I help you?

384
00:29:11,409 --> 00:29:13,809
You can make the envelopes,
if you like.

385
00:29:16,014 --> 00:29:19,313
- Why do they call her Fifine?
- It was Robert's idea.

386
00:29:19,517 --> 00:29:22,680
- He thinks Séraphine is too angelic.
- Robert?

387
00:29:22,887 --> 00:29:25,879
Robert Godard.
My brother's partner.

388
00:29:26,090 --> 00:29:29,491
- Yes, who I spoke to on the phone.
- That's it.

389
00:29:57,922 --> 00:30:00,914
You still haven't told me
what you think of Miléna.

390
00:30:01,125 --> 00:30:02,285
I hardly know her.

391
00:30:02,493 --> 00:30:04,256
After five years?

392
00:30:04,462 --> 00:30:07,090
She's a lovely friend,
but very closed.

393
00:30:07,298 --> 00:30:09,129
I think she's very beautiful.

394
00:30:09,334 --> 00:30:11,768
Strange that I never thought of her
in any other way.

395
00:30:11,970 --> 00:30:15,269
- Otherwise?
- Yes. If I were a man...

396
00:30:22,146 --> 00:30:23,374
What are you doing there?

397
00:30:27,952 --> 00:30:31,547
- Fifine. What are you doing?
- Admiring the landscape.

398
00:30:54,178 --> 00:30:56,305
I mean, I don't like her?

399
00:30:56,514 --> 00:30:58,277
- No. Why?
- Why not?

400
00:30:58,483 --> 00:30:59,745
It's like this.

401
00:30:59,951 --> 00:31:01,509
What if I send her away?

402
00:31:01,719 --> 00:31:03,983
- But why?
- Because he doesn't want to sleep with me.

403
00:31:04,188 --> 00:31:06,884
- What a mentality.
- I don't like pretentious people.

404
00:31:07,091 --> 00:31:09,116
I'm not pretentious...

405
00:31:10,194 --> 00:31:14,130
but I'm a virgin, Mr. Cesar.
I told you the other day.

406
00:31:15,066 --> 00:31:17,193
Are you mocking me?

407
00:31:17,402 --> 00:31:18,596
Jure.

408
00:31:18,803 --> 00:31:21,237
- What's that?
- That she's a virgin.

409
00:31:21,439 --> 00:31:23,964
Swear.
Are you mocking me?

410
00:31:24,175 --> 00:31:25,540
No, but...

411
00:31:25,743 --> 00:31:29,144
- I have the right not to want to.
- You have no right at all.

412
00:31:29,347 --> 00:31:31,212
He's not my type.

413
00:31:32,183 --> 00:31:33,673
You mean?

414
00:31:33,885 --> 00:31:36,718
- I don't want to say it.
- Say it anyway.

415
00:31:38,189 --> 00:31:41,784
- You'll get angry again.
- I swear I won't.

416
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:43,520
Well...

417
00:31:43,728 --> 00:31:46,128
I think you're a pig.

418
00:31:47,765 --> 00:31:49,960
And Johnny was going so fast
on his bike...

419
00:31:50,168 --> 00:31:52,898
that when he crossed
the village, no one saw.

420
00:31:53,104 --> 00:31:55,368
So, as there was
anything in the village...

421
00:31:55,573 --> 00:31:58,201
people said:
"It's Johnny coming through".

422
00:32:01,813 --> 00:32:03,212
How silly.

423
00:32:05,483 --> 00:32:08,919
- Do you think they're suspicious?
- Not Miléna, anyway.

424
00:32:09,120 --> 00:32:12,783
We'd better not be together
too long. You may notice.

425
00:32:12,991 --> 00:32:16,483
I have the impression that you
started looking after the little cousin.

426
00:32:16,694 --> 00:32:18,093
Yes. I have my plan.

427
00:32:18,296 --> 00:32:21,788
I'll take care of her and you'll take care of him.
We're in agreement, aren't we?

428
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:25,026
What if I fall in love with him?
He's handsome.

429
00:32:25,236 --> 00:32:27,295
Much better.
Beautiful and seductive.

430
00:32:27,505 --> 00:32:28,733
Much better.

431
00:32:28,940 --> 00:32:31,431
Almost as beautiful
as Luis Miguel Dominguin.

432
00:32:31,642 --> 00:32:35,134
- Who?
- Please, Robert. It's not funny.

433
00:32:38,950 --> 00:32:40,076
What's that?

434
00:32:40,385 --> 00:32:42,979
That's it. It's started again.
Curious, this mania.

435
00:32:59,804 --> 00:33:03,740
- Do you think that's normal?
- It's someone playing the organ.

436
00:33:03,941 --> 00:33:05,306
At midnight?

437
00:33:05,510 --> 00:33:08,911
Go and see, Robert.
This kind of thing terrifies me.

438
00:34:30,995 --> 00:34:33,259
Excuse my curiosity.
I thought it was a ghost.

439
00:34:33,464 --> 00:34:35,022
No. It's me.

440
00:34:35,233 --> 00:34:37,133
I like playing at night.
It's like an addiction.

441
00:34:37,335 --> 00:34:38,927
Nice addiction.

442
00:34:39,137 --> 00:34:41,662
- Was it "Jesus, Joy of Men"?
- Yes.

443
00:34:42,273 --> 00:34:44,798
There's something about this song...

444
00:34:45,576 --> 00:34:48,409
of suffering,
which has always fascinated me.

445
00:34:48,613 --> 00:34:50,638
Of threatened joy.

446
00:34:51,816 --> 00:34:53,147
Good.

447
00:34:53,751 --> 00:34:55,412
So, good night.

448
00:34:55,620 --> 00:34:57,247
Good evening.

449
00:35:23,147 --> 00:35:24,910
Prudence?

450
00:35:25,116 --> 00:35:26,481
Prudence?

451
00:35:27,485 --> 00:35:28,679
Open.

452
00:35:29,387 --> 00:35:31,378
I won't do anything.

453
00:35:31,589 --> 00:35:33,614
- I came to talk.
- No, I didn't.

454
00:35:33,824 --> 00:35:36,452
Prudence.
I'm going to break down the door.

455
00:35:37,328 --> 00:35:40,661
Prudence? Prudence?
Are you listening, Prudence?

456
00:35:51,876 --> 00:35:53,343
Mr. Cesar?

457
00:35:53,544 --> 00:35:55,637
Take my tray
and give me yours.

458
00:35:55,846 --> 00:35:58,110
Take Miss Fifine's,
I'll take Mr. Jean-Paul's.

459
00:35:58,316 --> 00:36:00,876
Why do you want to
take his?

460
00:36:01,085 --> 00:36:03,212
Don't you want to see Miss Fifine
in bed in the morning?

461
00:36:03,421 --> 00:36:06,288
- Yes, she is.
- She's pretty, isn't she?

462
00:36:06,490 --> 00:36:08,390
What about you?

463
00:36:09,093 --> 00:36:11,061
All right, then. Let's switch.

464
00:36:15,199 --> 00:36:16,723
Let's go.

465
00:36:16,934 --> 00:36:18,526
Come on, come on.

466
00:37:03,014 --> 00:37:04,311
Come in.

467
00:37:10,521 --> 00:37:13,388
- Good morning, Mr. Robert.
- What's this?

468
00:37:13,591 --> 00:37:15,957
Nothing, Mr. Godard.
I said good morning.

469
00:37:16,160 --> 00:37:19,323
- Who said that?
- My little finger.

470
00:37:19,530 --> 00:37:21,225
Come here, you.

471
00:37:21,866 --> 00:37:23,731
Put the tray down.

472
00:37:25,870 --> 00:37:28,930
You're good, Prudence.
You won't say anything.

473
00:37:29,140 --> 00:37:31,836
- But I can.
- It's a joke.

474
00:37:32,043 --> 00:37:33,510
It's only two days.

475
00:37:33,711 --> 00:37:36,509
- That's it.
- What do you mean, that's it?

476
00:37:36,714 --> 00:37:38,079
Listen.

477
00:37:38,282 --> 00:37:41,945
- I can buy your silence.
- Very nice.

478
00:37:42,153 --> 00:37:44,781
It's you who are beautiful.
Very.

479
00:37:48,225 --> 00:37:49,988
What would please her?

480
00:37:50,995 --> 00:37:52,826
I don't know.

481
00:37:53,030 --> 00:37:55,328
Don't be afraid.
I'll give you whatever you want.

482
00:37:55,533 --> 00:37:57,364
I'm not afraid.

483
00:38:14,185 --> 00:38:15,379
Hello?

484
00:38:15,586 --> 00:38:17,144
Miguel.

485
00:38:17,621 --> 00:38:19,452
A game of pool?

486
00:38:19,657 --> 00:38:22,057
I only played it in Indochina.

487
00:38:22,259 --> 00:38:23,920
But it's fine, yes.

488
00:38:24,128 --> 00:38:26,756
I'm going to finish getting dressed.
See you soon.

489
00:38:28,399 --> 00:38:32,267
You'll be nice
and wait for me to come and talk to you.

490
00:38:32,470 --> 00:38:35,030
- When?
- When?

491
00:38:35,239 --> 00:38:37,434
In his room, at midnight.

492
00:38:37,641 --> 00:38:39,666
I'll keep it under warranty.

493
00:38:39,877 --> 00:38:41,640
All right today?

494
00:38:41,846 --> 00:38:43,438
I'll see.

495
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:11,408
A real vacation.

496
00:39:12,243 --> 00:39:14,803
I never thought,
when I arrived.

497
00:39:15,012 --> 00:39:18,948
- Confess that you didn't like the idea.
- I didn't know her.

498
00:39:19,150 --> 00:39:21,778
Are you disappointed
with the inheritance?

