01:11:42,591 --> 01:11:45,583
Now I'm yours and
and I love you.

753
01:11:45,794 --> 01:11:48,354
What about her? Didn't you love her?

754
01:11:48,931 --> 01:11:51,297
I liked her. She's different.

755
01:11:52,701 --> 01:11:54,464
Whatever.

756
01:11:54,670 --> 01:11:56,570
What's with the comedy?

757
01:11:57,106 --> 01:11:58,698
Because of you.

758
01:11:59,308 --> 01:12:00,673
Mine?

759
01:12:01,076 --> 01:12:02,941
Passion at first sight.

760
01:12:03,145 --> 01:12:04,806
When I arrived on Saturday...

761
01:12:05,013 --> 01:12:06,776
you said, "Jean-Paul?"

762
01:12:06,982 --> 01:12:09,348
and I said yes, because
I wanted to be with you.

763
01:12:09,818 --> 01:12:13,777
Easy to say now.
I don't believe it, Jean-Paul.

764
01:12:13,956 --> 01:12:17,892
- You're talking nonsense.
- It's not nonsense. It's true.

765
01:12:20,562 --> 01:12:24,589
You're a buffoon.
You wanted an adventure, that's all.

766
01:12:25,467 --> 01:12:28,095
What amazes me is
Fifine being part of the arrangement.

767
01:12:28,303 --> 01:12:29,895
It wasn't agreed.

768
01:12:30,105 --> 01:12:33,836
- Yes. So she knew?
- It was give and take.

769
01:12:34,042 --> 01:12:35,737
You mean?

770
01:12:36,578 --> 01:12:39,376
If I revealed that I was her lover,
she wouldn't have Miguel...

771
01:12:39,581 --> 01:12:42,379
and if he'd known about me,
he wouldn't have dared.

772
01:12:42,584 --> 01:12:44,643
It would have been better.

773
01:12:44,853 --> 01:12:46,480
What nonsense.

774
01:12:46,688 --> 01:12:49,179
You should have known
that I would find out.

775
01:12:49,391 --> 01:12:52,087
- It didn't take long.
- How did you know?

776
01:12:52,294 --> 01:12:53,318
Prudence.

777
01:12:53,529 --> 01:12:56,498
I know, I know.
Dear Prudence.

778
01:12:57,032 --> 01:12:59,227
And the first thing he did
was to tell Miguel.

779
01:12:59,435 --> 01:13:01,494
Of course. Do you realize that?

780
01:13:01,703 --> 01:13:03,762
He opened a will
in front of a false brother.

781
01:13:03,972 --> 01:13:06,873
- So what? He went to get the police?
- You're out of your mind.

782
01:13:07,075 --> 01:13:10,602
- And where is Jean-Paul?
- He should be here soon.

783
01:13:10,813 --> 01:13:13,407
Saturday, on the phone,
he said he was coming Monday.

784
01:13:14,516 --> 01:13:17,417
- So everything falls into place?
- No.

785
01:13:17,986 --> 01:13:19,715
You stay with me.

786
01:13:19,922 --> 01:13:21,583
Not at all.

787
01:13:22,191 --> 01:13:23,158
And Fifine?

788
01:13:23,358 --> 01:13:25,349
- He's young. He'll console himself.
- How do you know?

789
01:13:25,561 --> 01:13:28,359
Fifine and I were friends
who slept together, and that was it.

790
01:13:28,564 --> 01:13:31,931
- She will console herself with Miguel.
- Miguel is a womanizer.

791
01:13:32,134 --> 01:13:34,398
He always had a lot of women.

792
01:13:34,603 --> 01:13:37,697
If he gets what he wants,
she will be unhappy.

793
01:13:37,906 --> 01:13:40,466
I'm convinced
that you love him.

794
01:13:42,144 --> 01:13:43,168
Fifine!

795
01:13:43,378 --> 01:13:46,472
- Come on, that's what's needed.
- Come quickly.

796
01:13:49,284 --> 01:13:50,546
Fifine!

797
01:13:51,086 --> 01:13:53,020
- Fifine!
- Fifine!

798
01:14:00,429 --> 01:14:03,592
- Cesar, have you seen Miss Fifine?
- Miss Fifine?

799
01:14:03,799 --> 01:14:05,562
- And you, Prudence?
- No, miss.

800
01:14:05,767 --> 01:14:07,291
- What happened?
- Fifine has disappeared.

801
01:14:07,503 --> 01:14:09,971
- I'll explain. She could kill herself.
- Kill herself?

802
01:14:10,172 --> 01:14:12,572
- Search before the brother arrives.
- What's wrong?

803
01:14:12,774 --> 01:14:14,173
- Does she have another brother?
- Yes, come on.

804
01:14:14,376 --> 01:14:16,037
Another brother?

805
01:14:23,752 --> 01:14:25,720
- It's my fault.
- No. It's mine.

806
01:14:25,921 --> 01:14:28,287
- I should say I loved her.
- Is this the time to argue?

807
01:14:28,490 --> 01:14:30,253
- It's my fault.
- No. It's Jean-Paul's.

808
01:14:30,459 --> 01:14:33,292
Robert, in fact.
Here's how his story turned out.

809
01:14:33,495 --> 01:14:34,985
- Miléna...
- That's it.

810
01:14:35,197 --> 01:14:37,290
If anything happens to him,
I won't forgive you.

811
01:14:37,499 --> 01:14:39,126
Let's look in the garden.

812
01:14:41,136 --> 01:14:42,467
Don't you love me anymore?

813
01:14:42,671 --> 01:14:44,798
I don't have time
to think about it.

814
01:14:49,444 --> 01:14:50,741
Fifine?

815
01:14:52,014 --> 01:14:53,413
Fifine?

816
01:15:01,423 --> 01:15:03,118
Miss Fifine!

817
01:15:12,768 --> 01:15:13,894
Miss Fifine!

818
01:15:14,169 --> 01:15:15,158
Fifine!

819
01:15:15,370 --> 01:15:16,667
Fifine!

820
01:15:17,306 --> 01:15:18,830
Miss Fifine!

821
01:15:21,176 --> 01:15:22,609
Fifine?

822
01:15:25,914 --> 01:15:27,245
Fifine?

823
01:15:31,853 --> 01:15:33,377
Fifine?

824
01:15:49,605 --> 01:15:51,835
Fifine disappeared.

825
01:15:52,908 --> 01:15:55,741
Maybe he's killing himself
for a fling.

826
01:15:58,180 --> 01:16:01,809
The four of us played the
of thoughtless love.

827
01:16:02,017 --> 01:16:04,281
We take ourselves for libertines.

828
01:16:18,800 --> 01:16:20,358
A car is coming.

829
01:16:58,073 --> 01:16:59,438
Good morning.

830
01:16:59,875 --> 01:17:01,172
Good morning.

831
01:17:05,213 --> 01:17:07,545
- Are you Mr. Jean-Paul?
- Yes.

832
01:17:07,749 --> 01:17:09,614
Mr. Jean-Paul!

833
01:17:13,388 --> 01:17:16,084
- Miguel Barran.
- Jean-Paul Brett-Juval. What's going on?

834
01:17:16,291 --> 01:17:17,622
Fifine disappeared.

835
01:17:17,826 --> 01:17:20,556
- My sister?
- What a time to arrive.

836
01:17:20,762 --> 01:17:23,026
- What are you doing there?
- Fifine has disappeared.

837
01:17:23,231 --> 01:17:26,200
- He's already said it. Explain.
- Do you remember that you wanted to kill yourself?

838
01:17:26,401 --> 01:17:28,733
- What about it?
- I'm afraid it'll start again.

839
01:17:28,937 --> 01:17:30,666
- Why?
- I'll explain later.

840
01:17:30,872 --> 01:17:32,931
- Are you Jean-Paul?
- Yes.

841
01:17:33,141 --> 01:17:35,234
I'm Miléna.
I'm sorry to see you like this.

842
01:17:35,444 --> 01:17:37,844
- The welcome is strange.
- Your sister has disappeared.

843
01:17:38,046 --> 01:17:39,274
- Did you look?
- Yes.

844
01:17:39,481 --> 01:17:41,449
- You too, Cesar?
- All that's missing is the basement.

845
01:17:41,650 --> 01:17:43,948
- The swimming pool.
- That's right. I'll check it out.

846
01:17:44,619 --> 01:17:46,985
- What can I do?
- Nothing.

847
01:17:47,589 --> 01:17:49,921
- I'll go back to the greenhouse and have a look.
- I'll come along.

848
01:17:50,125 --> 01:17:52,059
- You don't have to.
- I'm going anyway.

849
01:17:55,397 --> 01:17:57,797
- What's her name?
- Florence.

850
01:17:58,400 --> 01:18:00,800
- Do you know where Fifine is?
- Yes.

851
01:18:01,002 --> 01:18:02,697
- Do you know where Fifine is?
- Yes.

852
01:18:02,904 --> 01:18:04,735
Go and get it.

853
01:18:05,006 --> 01:18:07,031
Let's go. Go and get her.

854
01:18:07,242 --> 01:18:09,870
Tell her brother wants to see her.
Let's go!

855
01:19:28,490 --> 01:19:29,514
Fifine?

856
01:19:40,235 --> 01:19:42,703
Come along. Your brother is there.

857
01:20:55,810 --> 01:20:57,038
Jean-Paul.

858
01:20:57,245 --> 01:20:58,906
Come on, Fifine.

859
01:21:01,650 --> 01:21:03,880
Were you playing
hide and seek?

860
01:21:04,085 --> 01:21:06,349
Don't make fun of me, Jean-Paul.

861
01:21:06,554 --> 01:21:08,385
I'm very unhappy.

862
01:21:09,257 --> 01:21:10,485
You know...

863
01:21:10,692 --> 01:21:14,287
when you play a game,
there is always a loser.

864
01:21:15,830 --> 01:21:17,559
I've lost everything.

865
01:21:19,000 --> 01:21:20,331
Not at all.

866
01:21:21,036 --> 01:21:22,867
It was a joke.

867
01:21:23,405 --> 01:21:26,966
- So don't cry.
- Please prepare the lilac room...

868
01:21:27,175 --> 01:21:28,836
for Mr. Jean-Paul.

869
01:21:29,044 --> 01:21:31,604
- What tone is that?
- Run it.

870
01:21:31,813 --> 01:21:35,112
You don't lose
by waiting, you know?

871
01:21:36,685 --> 01:21:39,620
Leave them.
They don't need us anymore.

872
01:21:43,758 --> 01:21:44,918
Miléna.

873
01:21:46,661 --> 01:21:48,424
Do you have one for me?

874
01:22:02,210 --> 01:22:04,371
The first cigarette
after the scare...

875
01:22:04,579 --> 01:22:06,046
is the best.

876
01:22:06,247 --> 01:22:09,648
No. The best is after love.

877
01:22:09,851 --> 01:22:11,250
Yes.

878
01:22:12,187 --> 01:22:13,882
And with you.

879
01:22:14,389 --> 01:22:16,186
With you.
